description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic and motivated Approved/ Approved Experienced Clinical Coding Trainer with excellent communication skills to join our friendly clinical coding team. Reporting to the Clinical Coding Services Manager you will work alongside existing team leaders and auditors to deliver a comprehensive clinical coding training programme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A flexible approach to work is essential, as applicants may be required to work on other sites and in other areas within the Trust. The role will combine onsite and home based working. All applicants must be willing to maintain their skills by attendance on workshops and refresher training courses.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;7% RRP is payable for this role&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants without the necessary training qualification may be considered for a Trainee Trainer role and will be supported to achieve certification.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Helen Kielty&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Clinical Coding Services Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: helen.kielty@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 0151 604 7553&lt;/p&gt;
